                           \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                        \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n            \n    \n    \n        \n                    \n                        \n                                    \n\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSamsung\u0026#39;s smart TVs are finally set to receive its One UI, the unified operating system used throughout all its devices.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eBased on Samsung\u0026#39;s Tizen operating system, the update has been a long time coming, and will make it even easier to link your devices.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"samsung-brings-one-ui-to-tizen-powered-smart-tvs\"\u003e Samsung Brings One UI to Tizen-Powered Smart TVs \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFirst spotted by \u003ca href=\"https://www.sammobile.com/news/samsung-tv-one-ui-update-released-tizen-8-0/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eSamMobile\u003c/a\u003e, Samsung is following up on the information revealed at its Developer Conference in early October 2024.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe update brings One UI to Samsung smart TVs running Tizen OS, which will be bundled with the upcoming Tizen 8.0 update. One UI brings \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/best-one-ui-6-features-samsung-galaxy/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eSamsung\u0026#39;s smartphone interface\u003c/a\u003e to smart TVs and delivers some new features to boot.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor example, One UI will bring a new For You tab featuring personalized recommendations, along with Live and Apps tabs to help you find more content. The Apps tab should help unify your apps across devices, too.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI\u0026#39;m also interested to see Samsung Daily+, which Samsung is billing as \u0026#34;a lifestyle service hub that provides useful daily life experiences.\u0026#34; It\u0026#39;ll live on your smart TV Home screen after the update, and I imagine it\u0026#39;ll use your searches and other interactions to provide a content stream.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThat could be handy, but the phrasing also conjures up visions of Samsung and Bixby doling out useful life quotes and inspirational phrases in your living room.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eElsewhere, there\u0026#39;s a new Multi Control tool to connect multiple Samsung hardware devices to a single mouse and keyboard, plus deeper integration for Samsung SmartThings IoT devices.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"when-is-the-samsung-one-ui-update-landing-on-tizen-smart-tvs\"\u003e When Is the Samsung One UI Update Landing on Tizen Smart TVs? \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Samsung One UI update is rolling out, though there is no specific timeline for it to land on your TV. Samsung advises you to \u0026#34;keep your device up to date and regulary check for software updates.\u0026#34;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, there is one potential drawback to note: \u0026#34;Once you install this version of the OS, you cannot uninstall or revert back to the previous version.\u0026#34; In other words, you\u0026#39;re locked into One UI whether you like it or not, so consider whether you want the permanent upgrade before hitting update.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n \u003c/div\